# KeaBot Rules

## Execution Chain (Immutable Order)
DesignBot (Claude Opus 4.6) → EstimateBot (Sonnet 4.6) → PermitBot (Sonnet 4.6)

Each bot gates the next. No skipping. No parallel execution.

## Model Assignments
- DesignBot: `claude-opus-4-6` ONLY — never downgrade
- EstimateBot: `claude-sonnet-4-6`
- PermitBot: `claude-sonnet-4-6`
- KeaCore LLM brain: Sonnet 4.6 primary → GPT-4o fallback → Grok-2 secondary

## Anthropic Caching (Required)
Always use `ClaudeCachedClient` — never raw Anthropic SDK.
Apply `cache_control: {"type":"ephemeral"}` to ALL 4 blocks:
1. KeaBot MEP system prompt
2. Prisma schema overview
3. API request/response contract
4. CTC metadata

Each cacheable block must be under 1,024 tokens.

## Cache Metrics
Track in KeaBotRun Prisma model: `cacheCreationTokens`, `cacheReadTokens`, `cacheHit`
Target: 60–75% cache hit rate.

## PermitBot Jurisdictions
DC DCRA | Montgomery County MD | Prince George's County MD
Arlington County VA | Fairfax County VA | Alexandria VA | Baltimore City MD
Always include jurisdiction slug in permit requests.
